				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$f(x) = c + [\{ d - c\} /1 + \exp (b(\log (x) - \tilde{e}))]$$\end{document}f(x)=c+[{d-c}/1+exp(b(log(x)-e~))]), where b = slope at the inflection point, c = lower limit, d = upper limit and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\tilde{e} = \log (ED_{50} )$$\end{document}e~=log(ED50)) using the R package drc (version 2.5-12). ED50 with 90 % confidence intervals was determined by drc as part of the curve fitting. Differences in ED50 parameter values were determined between strains and p values generated by means of approximate t tests (Ritz and Streibig 2005). Data were visualized using the lattice (version 0.20-33) and latticeExtra (version 0.6-26) packages via the BPG package (P’ng et al. submitted; version 5.3.4). All error bars represent standard error of the mean. ED50 values were compared using inferential confidence intervals with Δ = 2 × ED50 90 % confidence range for Cyp1a1 to determine whether any gene(s) had an ED50 value statistically equivalent to Cyp1a1 (Beckstead 2008; Tryon and Lewis 2008).
